column6: A LOCAL RESIDENT REPORTED THAT A FEW SMALL TREES WERE BLOWN DOWN NEAR THE SOUTH END OF LAKE BURTON. (GSP)

column8: A FEW LIMBS UP TO 3 AND 4 INCHES IN DIAMETER FELL DURING A STORM GUST. TOPS OF TREES ON RIDGES WERE SEEN TO BE VIGOROUSLY SWAYING. (GSP)
MULTIPLE TREES AND POWER LINES DOWN ON BYNUM RD. (BMX)
